This paper is primarily focused on the training of neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). It also discusses the computational complexity of different variants of the backpropagation algorithm, which is relevant to the field of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses benchmark datasets such as MNIST and CIFAR-10, which are commonly used in the field of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the behavior of neural networks in physical systems, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence properties of different types of neural networks, which is relevant to the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
